
# GrainPalette - Rice Type Classification Documentation

## Project Overview
GrainPalette is a deep learning application for rice type classification using transfer learning with MobileNetV4 architecture.

## System Requirements
- Windows 8 or higher
- Two web browsers installed
- Bandwidth: 30 Mbps minimum
- Python 3.8+
- TensorFlow 2.x
- Flask framework

## Model Architecture
- Base Model: MobileNetV4
- Transfer Learning: Pre-trained on ImageNet
- Custom Dense Layers: Added for rice classification
- Input Shape: 224x224x3 (RGB images)
- Output Classes: 5 rice types

## Rice Types Supported
1. Arborio
2. Basmati  
3. Jasmine
4. Brown Rice
5. Wild Rice

## Technical Implementation
- Frontend: React with TypeScript
- Backend: Flask Python application
- Model: TensorFlow/Keras (rice.h5)
- Image Processing: PIL/OpenCV
- Data Augmentation: ImageDataGenerator

## Usage Scenarios
1. Farmers' Crop Planning
2. Research and Agricultural Extension
3. Home Gardening and Education

## File Structure
- /src/data/ - Training and validation datasets
- /src/forms/ - Form components
- /src/static/ - CSS and static assets  
- /src/templates/ - HTML templates
- /src/Training/ - Model files including rice.h5
- app.py - Flask application
- rice-classification.ipynb - Training notebook
